reviews_data.review_text: My favorite place in Charlotte. The sweet tea is the best and the workers are so kind. Honestly spend hours doing work there. Trivia on Wednesday there is the best!

I recently visited Rhino Deli Market and had a mixed experience. The lady at the cashier was incredibly nice, and another gentleman who was there was also very respectful and friendly. They really made us feel welcome with their warm customer service.

However, our interaction with the cook was less pleasant. We arrived to place our order at 7:55 PM, unaware that the kitchen was closing at 8:00 PM. As soon as we approached the cook, he seemed quite annoyed and said, "Come on man, we close in 4 minutes." Although he did take our order after a minute of complaining, his attitude was noticeably different from the rest of the staff. When I returned to check if our food was ready, he responded with, "Give me 1 minute, Bro!"--again, not the most polite way to handle a customer.

Despite this, the food was excellent, and the other staff members were great. However, customer service is key, and this experience with the cook stood out in contrast to the otherwise positive vibe of the deli. I hope the management can address this, as it would make the experience even better.

Overall, I would recommend Rhino Deli Market for its great food and mostly wonderful staff, but there's definitely room for improvement in how all customers are treated.
Great store, staff, food & bev options

We're lucky to live right across the street from Rhino Market & Deli Uptown, so we find ourselves there often--especially for trivia nights on Wednesdays! Whenever our schedule allows, we're there, and it's always a great time.

A big shoutout to our favorite Rhino team member, Guthrie! He's the best--super kind, funny, and always makes us feel welcome. He remembers our names, greets us with a smile, and sends us off with well wishes every time.

The deli food is consistently delicious, but the grab-and-go chicken salad is next-level good!

If we had one small suggestion, it would be to see some domestic beers or seltzers on draft, since we're not craft beer folks. Draft kombucha would be a fantastic addition too.

Rhino Market is a gem in our neighborhood, and we're so glad to have it as our local go-to spot!
